The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Bengal | Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                         BRIEFS
                  
	Calcutta, Dec. 11: Buddhadeb Bhattacharjee today expressed hope about a positive response from the National Council for Teacher Education on the crisis in the Primary Teachers Training Institutes. The court had declared them illegal. He has also sought the Prime Ministers help to end the crisis.        
	Purulia: An elephant was electrocuted when its trunk touched a high-tension wire on the outskirts of a Purulia village on Wednesday night. As it groaned in pain, the herd trumpeted in unison till daybreak, giving villagers a scare.        
	Calcutta: The gov-ernment will set up six police stations along the states coastline and arm the personnel with AK-47 rifles and night-vision glasses. The terrorists who attacked Mumbai had come by the sea.                                                                                                                                                                   
